<book xmlns:exforms="http://www.exforms.org/exf/1-0" xmlns:xxi="http://orbeon.org/oxf/xml/xinclude" xmlns:ev="http://www.w3.org/2001/xml-events" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xforms="http://www.w3.org/2002/xforms" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:pipeline="java:org.orbeon.oxf.processor.pipeline.PipelineFunctionLibrary" xmlns:fr="http://orbeon.org/oxf/xml/form-runner" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xxforms="http://orbeon.org/oxf/xml/xforms" xmlns:xbl="http://www.w3.org/ns/xbl">
    <details>
        <title>Surely You're Joking, Mr. Feynman!</title>
        <author>Richard Feynman</author>
        <language>en</language>
        <link>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surely_You're_Joking,_Mr._Feynman!</link>
        <rating/>
        <publication-year>1985</publication-year>
        <review>&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="line-height: 20px; font-family: sans-serif; "/&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;"Surely You're Joking, Mr. Feynman!": Adventures of a Curious Character&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#160;is an edited collection of reminiscences by the&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nobel_Prize_in_Physics" title="Nobel Prize in Physics" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Nobel Prize&lt;/a&gt;-winning physicist&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Feynman" title="Richard Feynman" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Richard Feynman&lt;/a&gt;. The book, released in 1985, covers a variety of instances in Feynman's life. Some are lighthearted in tone, such as his fascination with&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Safe-cracking" title="Safe-cracking" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;safe-cracking&lt;/a&gt;, fondness for topless bars, and ventures into art and&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samba" title="Samba" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;samba&lt;/a&gt;&#160;music. Others cover more serious material, including his work on the&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manhattan_Project" title="Manhattan Project" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Manhattan Project&lt;/a&gt;&#160;(during which his first wife Arline Greenbaum died of&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuberculosis" title="Tuberculosis" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;tuberculosis&lt;/a&gt;) and his critique of the science&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Education_in_Brazil" title="Education in Brazil" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;education system in Brazil&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;The anecdotes were edited from&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tape_recorder" title="Tape recorder" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;taped&lt;/a&gt;&#160;conversations that Feynman had with his close friend and drumming partner&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ralph_Leighton" title="Ralph Leighton" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Ralph Leighton&lt;/a&gt;. Its surprise success led to a sequel entitled&#160;&lt;i&gt;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/What_Do_You_Care_What_Other_People_Think%3F" title="What Do You Care What Other People Think?" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;What Do You Care What Other People Think?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/i&gt;, also taken from Leighton's taped conversations.&#160;&lt;i&gt;Surely You're Joking, Mr. Feynman!&lt;/i&gt;&#160;sold more than 500,000 copies.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="margin-top: 0.4em; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.5em; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1.5em; "&gt;The title derives from a woman's response at&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Princeton_University" title="Princeton University" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Princeton University&lt;/a&gt;&#160;when, after she asked the newly-arrived Feynman if he wanted cream or lemon in his tea, he absentmindedly requested both&#160;(not knowing that they would&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" class="mw-redirect" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Curdling" title="Curdling" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;curdle&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;br clear="none"/&gt;&lt;br clear="none"/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 11px; line-height: 15px; "&gt;Text is available under the&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" rel="license" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Text_of_Creative_Commons_Attribution-ShareAlike_3.0_Unported_License" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike License&lt;/a&gt;; additional terms may apply. See&#160;&lt;a shape="rect" href="http://wikimediafoundation.org/wiki/Terms_of_Use" style="text-decoration: none; color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: initial; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; "&gt;Terms of Use&lt;/a&gt;&#160;for details.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br clear="none"/&gt;</review>
